observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
 a. BAC and its TWG to: (i) revisit the guidelines and provisions of the updated 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and GPPB Resolutions to ensure that all procurement activities undertaken by the Municipality are strictly in accordance with the provisions of the updated 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; (ii) be cautious and exercise prudence in the examination of eligibility and technical documents submitted by the prospective bidders in faithful adherence to relevant provisions of the updated 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 to prevent the award of contract to ineligible contractors/suppliers; (iii) immediately submit the lacking bidding documents to the Audit Team to arrive at a decision in audit; (iv) ensure strict compliance with the provisions set forth in Rule No. 36 of the IRR of Republic Act No. 9502 and EO No. 49 regarding the procurement of drugs and medicines; and (v) strictly comply with the prescribed period of furnishing the COA Auditor copies of contracts including the documentary requirements to facilitate timely review and evaluation as prescribed by COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009 and COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012;
 b. Municipal Accountant to immediately submit the noted lacking supporting documents and henceforth ensure that all claims are duly supported with proper and complete supporting documents, as required under COA Circular No. 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012, before processing claims for payment, and henceforth ensure that all claims are duly supported with complete and proper documentation before processing of payment to establish the validity and propriety of transactions;
 c. Municipal Engineer to closely monitor the project implementation and ensure strict compliance with the construction schedules so that projects are implemented efficiently and effectively in accordance with the approved plans and specifications within the contract duration; and
 d. Municipal Treasurer to ensure that claimants other than the authorized representative of contractor are duly supported with SPA or written authorizations from the supplier/contractor and with proofs of identification.

In view thereof, we recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
i. analyze and review the outstanding stale checks and prepare the necessary adjusting JEV to present the correct account balances of the Cash in Bank account;
ii. exhaust all the possible remedies to collect the receivables and make formal demand to the concerned AOs for the settlement/liquidation of cash advances and fund transfers and make a formal request for the writing-off, together with the necessary supporting documents, of unliquidated cash advances of those who are already deceased, in accordance with COA Circular No. 2016-005; 
iii. strictly monitor the grant of cash advance by issuing certification that previous cash advances have been liquidated and accounted for in the books to prevent the grant of additional cash advances to those employees and officers with outstanding cash advances and ensure that the attached list to the grant and liquidation of cash advances are duly supported with proper and complete supporting documents, such as ObRs, to establish the validity, propriety and legality of the transactions;
iv. refrain from booking-up as CIP accounts the contract price of the projects yet to be billed with the definition of the account set forth in Annex B of COA Circular No. 2015-009 and make the necessary adjustments to correct the actual balance of the CIP and PPE accounts affected by the non-transfer of completed project and immediate recognition of not yet billed projects to the CIP account;
v. reclassify the portion of the long-term loan which is due for settlement within twelve months from reporting date as current liabilities in the Statement of Financial Position;
vi. verify the validity of the payables and send confirmation letters for balances with identified claimants or creditors;
vii. exert effort to retrieve the documents of unverified payables or those without details to properly classify and the amounts recorded; and
viii. analyze the transactions and prepare the necessary accounting entries to adjust the affected accounts to fairly present the Financial Statements.

We also recommended that the Municipal Budget Officer duly prepare the ObRs for all transactions to ensure that valid and legal expenditures and obligations are taken up in the accounts of the current fiscal year pursuant to Section 119 of PD No. 1445.

Lastly, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor: (i) demand the contractor viable remedies to continue the implementation of abandoned projects otherwise, institute appropriate legal actions/sanctions/penalties applicable under the existing rules and regulations against the contractor who failed to deliver and complete the project in accordance with the contract agreement/terms; and (ii) make representations with the source agency for the possible reprogramming of the unexpended balances to other new PPAs otherwise, cause the immediate return/refund of said balances.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:
BAC and its TWG to: (i) be cautious and exercise prudence in the examination of eligibility and technical documents submitted by the prospective bidders in faithful adherence to relevant provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 to prevent the award of contract to ineligible contractors/suppliers;          (ii) ensure that all procurement activities undertaken by the Municipality are strictly in accordance with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184, in all stages of the procurement, for proper evaluation and assessment of the eligibility as to legal, technical and financial capacities of the prospective bidders; (iii) immediately submit the lacking bidding documents to the Audit Team to arrive at a decision in audit; and (iv) henceforth, submit perfected contracts, together with all supporting documents, within five working days after its approval and ensure that perfected contracts are properly and completely documented before submitting the same to the Audit Team;
BAC: (i) to revisit the updated guidelines and provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and GPPB Resolutions to ensure that the complete set of bid documents offered for sale to prospective bidders contains the necessary information for an efficient, transparent and economical procurement;             (ii) through the BAC Secretariat to a) invite, in addition to the representative of the COA, at least two (2) qualified observers with knowledge, experience and expertise on the procurement at hand, in all stages of the procurement process, five (5) days prior to the activity; b) post in the PhilGEPS website and in any conspicuous places within the premises of the LGU copies of the Notices of Award, Approved Contracts and Notices to Proceed within the prescribed period; (iii) ensure that the submitted technical and eligibility requirements are original or certified true copies; (iv) ensure that bidding documents available for sale to prospective bidders are complete as to details to ensure that requirements/specifications of the projects are properly addressed and clear to the prospective bidders; and (v) prioritize the undertaking of procurement process to avoid postponements and/or delays;
Municipal Engineer to: (i) prepare the ABC in the format prescribed under DPWH Department Order No. 197 s. 2016; (ii) ensure that variation and/or change orders are properly evaluated and documented to ascertain the reasonableness of the additional/change in work items pursuant to Annex E of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; and (iii) closely monitor the project implementations and ensure that projects are implemented and completed within the contract duration, otherwise, compute for liquidated damages (LD) therein;
Municipal Accountant to: (i) immediately submit the lacking supporting documents in the claims for payment, and henceforth ensure that all payments are supported with complete and proper documents before processing for payment; and (ii) impose and issue order of payment for LDs as determined and recommended by the Municipal Engineer; and
Municipal Treasurer to ensure that claimants, other than the authorized representative of contractor, are supported with written authorization from the supplier/contractor and supported with proofs of identification.

